{"parse":{"title":"Spiral approach","pageid":980688,"revid":843180651,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><dl><dd><i>See also <a href=\"/wiki/Spiral_model\" title=\"Spiral model\">spiral model</a></i>, a <a href=\"/wiki/Software_development_process\" title=\"Software development process\">software development approach</a>.<i></i></dd></dl>\n<p>The <b><a href=\"/wiki/Spiral\" title=\"Spiral\">spiral</a> approach</b> is a technique often used in teaching or <a href=\"/wiki/Textbook\" title=\"Textbook\">textbooks</a> where first the basic facts of a subject are learned, without worrying about details.  Then as learning progresses, more and more details are introduced, while at the same time they are related to the basics which are reemphasized many times to help enter them into <a href=\"/wiki/Long-term_memory\" title=\"Long-term memory\">long-term memory</a>.  This principle is somewhat similar to the <a href=\"/wiki/Inverted_pyramid_(journalism)\" title=\"Inverted pyramid (journalism)\">inverted pyramid</a> method used in writing news stories, and the game <a href=\"/wiki/20_questions\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"20 questions\">20 questions</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Spiral_approach&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20150628045031/http://www.leaningpinesoftware.com/spiral.shtml\">The spiral approach applied to math</a></li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20120204041202/http://www.krl.caltech.edu/~prezeau/TeachPhilo.pdf\">One teacher's description of how he uses the spiral approach (pdf file)</a></li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.av8n.com/physics/spiral-approach.htm\">The Spiral Approach to Thinking and Learning by John Denker</a></li></ul>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"/wiki/File:Nuvola_apps_bookcase.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Stub icon\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a5/Nuvola_apps_bookcase.svg/30px-Nuvola_apps_bookcase.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a5/Nuvola_apps_bookcase.svg/45px-Nuvola_apps_bookcase.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a5/Nuvola_apps_bookcase.svg/60px-Nuvola_apps_bookcase.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"128\" data-file-height=\"128\" /></a></td><td><i>This article relating to <a href=\"/wiki/Education\" title=\"Education\">education</a> is a <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Stub\" title=\"Wikipedia:Stub\">stub</a>. You can help Wikipedia by <a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Spiral_approach&amp;action=edit\">expanding it</a>.</i><div class=\"plainlinks hlist navbar mini\" style=\"position: absolute; right: 15px; display: none;\"><ul><li class=\"nv-view\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template:Edu-stub\" title=\"Template:Edu-stub\"><abbr title=\"View this template\">v</abbr></a></li><li class=\"nv-talk\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template_talk:Edu-stub\" title=\"Template talk:Edu-stub\"><abbr title=\"Discuss this template\">t</abbr></a></li><li class=\"nv-edit\"><a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Template:Edu-stub&amp;action=edit\"><abbr title=\"Edit this template\">e</abbr></a></li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw1321\nCached time: 20180907162022\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.032 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.041 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 36/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010